                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="nasta_liq" medium="ink">
                        Written in clear <material>black</material> nasta‘līq with subheaders in <material>red</material>.
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="headpiece"><label>Illumination:</label> Folio <locus from="1b" to="1b">1b</locus> bears a scalloped domed headpiece with gilt palmette foliate scrollwork on an ultramarine ground and an uninscribed central cartouche, and four vertical radiating lines.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="marginal"><label>Floral Margins:</label> Polychrome hand-painted margins feature floral scrollwork .</decoNote>                     
                     <decoNote type="marginal"><label>Applied Borders:</label> Strips of indigo, salmon pink, and slate-coloured paper, measuring ~9–10 mm wide, surround all central compositions and and the outer margins on all folios.</decoNote> 
                     <decoNote type="marginal"><label>Ruling:</label> Folios <locus from="1b" to="2a>">1b and 2a</locus> ruled in <material>gold</material> outlined with thin black lines, and surrounded by another single line. The margins of folios <locus from="2b">2b</locus> onwards ruled with single lines of ultramarine blue.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
